# .phi-scanignore — PhiScan exclusion patterns
# Syntax: gitignore-style (via Python pathspec library)
#
# Rules:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Blank lines are ignored
#   - Patterns match relative to the repository root
#   - Trailing / matches directories only: node_modules/
#   - * matches anything except /: *.pyc
#   - ** matches any number of directories: **/test_data/
#   - ! prefix negates a pattern (re-include): !important_config.yml
#   - Leading / anchors to repo root: /build/ matches only root-level build/
#   - No leading / matches at any depth: __pycache__/ at depth 1 or depth 10
#
# Reference: phi-scan explain ignore

# Dependencies
node_modules/
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/
.tox/

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
target/

# IDE and editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# Version control
.git/

# PhiScan's own files
.phi-scanner/
*.db
*.sqlite3

# Common non-code directories
.terraform/
.serverless/
